&lt;div class=&quot;public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr&quot; data-offset-key=&quot;crt3h-0-0&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Chicago Sun-Times is a distinctly Chicago news organization, with a laser focus on telling stories that matter to the working people of Chicago. We are seeking an experienced sports reporter to lead coverage of the Chicago White Sox. This role requires a journalist who can break news, deliver insightful analysis, cultivate sources throughout the organization, and connect with readers across multiple platforms. The successful candidate will be expected to travel with the team, produce enterprise reporting, and contribute to broader Sun-Times sports coverage when needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide factual, accurate, fair and balanced coverage of the White Sox organization —&amp;nbsp; including its players, front office and ownership, and Major League Baseball —&amp;nbsp;plus be versatile enough to help out on our other major beats&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Break news, both on the Sox and MLB&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write a mix of stories, including “instant gamers,” analysis stories, and longer human-interest features, including features for the Sun-Times’ innovative Sports Sunday edition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the face of our White Sox coverage, both in print and online through podcasts and, in some cases, video reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the Sun-Times audience and visual teams to develop video, infographics, and other interactive elements that engage both digital and print readers — with some of these elements to be used to promote stories on social media&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use social media to interact with fans, including during games, and to promote our work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
